elements.title: coat of arms of Jersey
elements.contents: ... that the coat of arms of Jersey was allowed to be featured on its stamps during the occupation in World War II, with the Germans unaware that it was also the royal arms of England?

elements.title: Ingrid Haubold
elements.contents: ... that when Ingrid Haubold recorded the role of Senta in Wagner's Der fliegende Holländer, reviewer Alan Blyth found "a certain raw edge" of her soprano voice apt for the role?

elements.title: Mumbai Mirror
elements.contents: ... that 200,000 copies of the Mumbai Mirror were distributed on its inaugural print run in 2005, giving it the second-largest circulation in Mumbai?

elements.title: Lisa Barbelin

elements.title: Ripon Spa Baths
elements.contents: ... that Ripon Spa Baths is the only spa in the United Kingdom to have been ceremonially opened by a member of the royal family?

elements.title: Leila Velez
elements.contents: ... that one of Leila Velez's reasons for expanding her Brazilian beauty-salon company is to fight racism against black women and their natural afro-textured hair?

elements.title: Featherdale Wildlife Park
